ass="container brag-bar"> <div class="row"> <div class="col-md-4"><blockquote>"TeamHeadquarters is the the one consolidated tool that our department relies on to run our service desk, our projects... our business."<small>Metro Health - Michigan</small></blockquote></div><div class="col-md-4"><blockquote>"TeamHeadquarters allows all our customer contact, project, support, and technical information to be accessed in one place. This immediately improved our customer satisfaction by 26%."<small>Extendicare, Ontario</small></blockquote></div><div class="col-md-4"><blockquote>"By implementing THQ we consolidated all helpdesk and project management systems into one and eliminated all the existing systems."<small>Onslow Memorial Hospital</small></blockquote></div></div><!--</div><div class="container-fluid well"> <img src="/img/healthcarecusts.png" alt="health care customer logo bar" class="center-block"> </div><div class="container"> --> <div class="row"> <div class="col-md-8"> <h1>TeamHeadquarters for Healthcare</h1> <p class="lead">Healthcare organizations struggle to keep costs low and deliver the best services possible. IT Departments are tasked with providing excellent enabling technologies quickly and cost effectively. Lower costs and better service can be achieved with any of three methods:</p><div class="media panel"> <h4 class="media-heading">1. Development and Execution of Good IT Strategies</h4> <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-th pull-left media-object" style="font-size: 6em; color: rgb(43, 73, 161); padding: 10px 5px 0px 0px;"></span> <p>This is integral to any modern organization and IT Managers and CIOs are responsible for helping the organization achieve its goals. The primary goals of any IT Management group are to reduce costs and improve service. To achieve these goals require a sound strategy: Centralize all IT work into a single solution to manage resources effectively, increase project throughput, improve customer service, enact policy and procedure guidelines for the healthcare staff and direct all IT requests, internal or external, through the system. TeamHeadquarters clients have implemented this simple five-part strategy multiple times, which has resulted in lower costs and better service.</p><p>TeamHeadquarters provides you with the means to execute your IT Business Strategy with maximum efficiency, effectiveness and precision.</p></div><div class="media panel"> <h4 class="media-heading">2. Control of External Vendor Involvement</h4> <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-export pull-left media-object" style="font-size: 6em; color: rgb(43, 73, 161); padding: 10px 5px 0px 0px;" ></span> <p>IT Managers have greater cost control of external work and easily manage HIMS support when a centralized system is used to generate requests and manage the involvement of external vendors.</p><p>With TeamHeadquarters' single-system approach, all project work and support requests for internal and external vendors can be centrally managed.</p></div><div class="media panel"> <h4 class="media-heading">3. Centralization of all IT Work into a Single System</h4> <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-random pull-left media-object" style="font-size: 6em; color: rgb(43, 73, 161); padding: 10px 10px 0px 0px;"></span> <p>Centralizing all IT work into a single system helps define priorities, identify solutions and allocate resources. Consolidation will reduce costs and, when combined with centralization of IT services, will take the work from external vendors.</p><p>With TeamHeadquarters, you'll consolidate many of your IT work management systems &#8212; the systems that make sense to consolidate &#8212; and remove the data silos in your organization. The results are significant and include improved customer service, lower costs, fewer lost or mishandled service requests and improved staff morale.</p></div><a href="http://signup.entry.com/trial-demo-both-teamheadquarters" class="btn btn-success btn-lg">Free 15 Day Trial</a> <a href="http://signup.entry.com/demonstration" class="btn btn-success btn-lg">Demonstration</a> <a href="http://signup.entry.com/quotation" class="btn btn-info btn-lg">Project Estimate</a> </div><div class="col-md-4 alert alert-info"> <div class="thumbnail"> <a href="#" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#ebook"><img src="/img/it-managers-guide-itil.png" alt="IT managers guide to ITIL" class="img-responsive"></a> <h4 class="thumbnail-label text-center">ITSM eBook<br><small>click to download</small></h4> <div class="modal fade" id="ebook" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="ebook" aria-hidden="true"> <div class="modal-dialog modal-lg"> <div class="modal-content"> <div class="modal-body"> <iframe src="http://signup.entry.com/download-it-managers-guidebook-to-implementing-itil" width="858" height="650" style="border:none;"></iframe> </div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div id="footer"> <?php include '../public_html/includes/footer.html';?> </div></body></html>